SIMPLE: stridulous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stridulous
<hw>Strid"u*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stridulus</ets>. See <er>Strident</er>.]</ety> <def>Making a
shrill, creaking sound.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Sarmatian boor driving his <qex>stridulous</qex> cart.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stridulous laryngitis</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a
form of croup, or laryngitis, in children, associated with dyspnoea,
occurring usually at night, and marked by crowing or stridulous
breathing.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strife</ent>⟦br⟧
